{"id":21979,"date":"2024-01-19T18:02:36","date_gmt":"2021-05-19T12:32:36","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=21979"},"modified":"2023-10-03T13:16:35","modified_gmt":"2023-10-03T07:46:35","slug":"minimalist-home-design-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/minimalist-home-design-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"11 Minimalist Home Design Ideas To Embrace Simplicity"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Let\u2019s embrace the clean design lines and gorgeous simplicity of home design with these 11 iconic minimalist design ideas<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cSimplicity is the ultimate sophistication.\u201d -Leonardo da Vinci.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Minimalism is an art movement that promotes extreme spareness and simplicity. While the minimalist style in architecture and interiors has been around since the 1920s, it has gained popularity of late. Homeowners are increasingly picking clean design lines, overdramatic ideas, light furniture over bulky pieces, and practical styles over good-looking elements.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>All these led to a design revolution that epicentres \u2018less is more\u2019. But minimalist design is not just about what\u2019s spare; it is also about carving a beautiful design consciousness that is simple but never boring. So, if you are thinking of embracing a minimalist home design, we are here to guide you and help you through this journey of discovering simplicity at its best.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Lets plan your home interiors together, speak to designers now\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/28124401\/lets-plan-home-interiors-together.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>But first, there are two very essential steps that you need to take before going ahead in our minimalist interior design voyage.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Get Ready To Let Go Of The Extras: <\/strong>A minimalist home design is one that has only the bare essentials. So, if you are going for a minimalist makeover, get rid of the extras in your home.&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Get Ready To Reduce What You Consider Essential: <\/strong>While opting for a minimalist home design, you must be prepared to redefine your \u2018essentials\u2019. You need to remind yourself to invest in things that you will really need.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you are aware of the steps you need to take to introduce minimalist design into your life, let\u2019s explore tips relating to minimalist home design to make your home sassy!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Always Choose Neutral Colours For Your Rooms<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A minimalist home design should have a monochrome neutral colour palette that is easy to understand. The minimalist design seeks to simplify by adding subtle colour choices. White, beige, etc., are the most common colour schemes for minimalist home designs. You can, however, use accent elements in the room to keep the place dynamic. But overall, the dominant colour scheme should be a monochrome tone that creates airy, bright and elegant spaces. The minimalist design also uses aqua nude tones that add understated elegance to areas.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174444\/minimalist-living-room-with-beige-colour.jpg\" alt=\"White living room in minimalist home design with a light grey sofa and rug creates airy, bright and elegant spaces.\" class=\"wp-image-21989\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174444\/minimalist-living-room-with-beige-colour.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174444\/minimalist-living-room-with-beige-colour-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174444\/minimalist-living-room-with-beige-colour-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174444\/minimalist-living-room-with-beige-colour-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A minimalist living room with a beige colour scheme<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">You Cannot Deny Clean Design Lines In Minimalist Home Designs<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Minimalist home designs require the use of clean design lines to create plain and uncluttered spaces. Clean design lines have smooth and functional design sensibilities such as flat surfaces, unpatterned furnishings, limited accessories, etc. This kitchen uses a monochrome off-white tone with soft, uniform surfaces. The handleless cabinets, sleek pendant lights and light-coloured flooring combine to create a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/modern-minimalist-kitchen-designs\/\">modern minimalist kitchen design<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174450\/off-white-minimalist-home-design-for-kitchen.jpg\" alt=\"Off-white island kitchen in minimalist home design with a breakfast countertop and pendant lights look sleek.\" class=\"wp-image-21990\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174450\/off-white-minimalist-home-design-for-kitchen.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174450\/off-white-minimalist-home-design-for-kitchen-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174450\/off-white-minimalist-home-design-for-kitchen-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174450\/off-white-minimalist-home-design-for-kitchen-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">An off-white minimalist kitchen design with modular, handleless cabinets<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Use Woodwork To Bring A Twist To Your Minimalist Home Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/living-and-dining-room-designs\/\">living-cum-dining room<\/a> has a minimalist home design with plenty of woodwork. Wooden furniture pieces are an essential element of traditional Indian interior design. Mixing it with a modern minimalist design can result in a striking amalgamation. The wooden sofa, the wooden TV unit, the swing and the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/dining-room-interiors\/dining-table-designs\/\">dining table<\/a> exude natural vibes in the space, which has a white monochrome minimalist design.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174457\/small-minimalist-home-designed-in-wood.jpg\" alt=\"Small minimalist home design, white living cum dining area with wooden tv unit, swing and dining table exude natural vibes.\" class=\"wp-image-21991\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174457\/small-minimalist-home-designed-in-wood.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174457\/small-minimalist-home-designed-in-wood-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174457\/small-minimalist-home-designed-in-wood-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174457\/small-minimalist-home-designed-in-wood-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">An Indian minimalist living-cum-dining area with gorgeous wooden furniture sets<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Make Statements With Monochrome Artwork For Minimalist Home Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Minimalist home designs can sometimes feel too understated; hence, you must make confident design decisions to spice up your minimalist interiors. For example, monochrome artwork in the living room can fill the void. Don\u2019t overdo the room elements; else, things might get busy and become counterintuitive. You can go with a single or a couple of striking art pieces.&nbsp;<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174420\/minimalist-and-luxury-living-space-fashionable-home-design.jpg\" alt=\"Minimalist and luxury living space fashionable home designed with monochrome artwork lends a striking look.\" class=\"wp-image-21985\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174420\/minimalist-and-luxury-living-space-fashionable-home-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174420\/minimalist-and-luxury-living-space-fashionable-home-design-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174420\/minimalist-and-luxury-living-space-fashionable-home-design-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174420\/minimalist-and-luxury-living-space-fashionable-home-design-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A white living room with minimalist monochrome artwork<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Looking for Modular Kitchen Interiors\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/05143011\/looking-for-modular-kitchen.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Or You Can Go Nominal With Your Minimalist Home Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Embrace minimalist design by decorating your bedroom like in this image. It uses white as the minimalist monochrome colour scheme with a laminated white nightstand. The white brick cladding acts as an accent element in the room. The primary essential furniture in the room and artwork complete the look of this room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174409\/bedroom-interior-in-minimalist-style.jpg\" alt=\"White bedroom home interior in a minimalist design lends aesthetic look with brick cladding accent wall and wooden flooring.\" class=\"wp-image-21983\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174409\/bedroom-interior-in-minimalist-style.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174409\/bedroom-interior-in-minimalist-style-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174409\/bedroom-interior-in-minimalist-style-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174409\/bedroom-interior-in-minimalist-style-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A beautiful minimalist bedroom with a white colour scheme and brick cladding accent wall<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Related Article <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/modern-minimalistic-bedroom-designs\/\">Modern Minimalistic Bedroom Designs<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Pendant Lights Can Make Great Minimalist Home Design Statement<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A minimalist home design may feel expressionless at times. You can try adding elements that go with the interior theme while adding a character to the space. For this, lighting plays an integral role. You can, therefore, opt for modern fixtures like pendant lights, floor lamps, etc. Light fixtures bring personality to places.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174439\/minimalist-home-interior-design-with-pendant-light.jpg\" alt=\"Living room in minimalist home interior design with classic furniture and pendant light brings personality to places.\" class=\"wp-image-21988\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174439\/minimalist-home-interior-design-with-pendant-light.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174439\/minimalist-home-interior-design-with-pendant-light-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174439\/minimalist-home-interior-design-with-pendant-light-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174439\/minimalist-home-interior-design-with-pendant-light-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A living room\u2019s seating area with an elegant, minimalist pendant light<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"15 Essential Rules for Minimalist Home Interior Design\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/k6aHqwLlUz8?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Play With Textiles To Add Vigour To Your Minimalist Home Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Rugs, carpets and throws bring a new dimension to places, especially in minimalist home designs where everything else is subdued. The rug in this room introduces a mix of patterns and a minimalist design that can get tricky if not used wisely.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174509\/white-living-room-in-minimalist-style-for-indian-homes.jpg\" alt=\"Minimalist home design India, White living room design looks sleek with a blue rug and brown sofa.\" class=\"wp-image-21993\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174509\/white-living-room-in-minimalist-style-for-indian-homes.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174509\/white-living-room-in-minimalist-style-for-indian-homes-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174509\/white-living-room-in-minimalist-style-for-indian-homes-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174509\/white-living-room-in-minimalist-style-for-indian-homes-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A white, uncluttered living room design with an accent blue rug for the seating area<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Related Article <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/minimalistic-living-room\/\">Minimalistic Living Room<\/a><br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">You Can Blend Rustic And Minimalist Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to pull off an unconventional minimalist design theme for your home, you can go with this awe-inspiring rustic-cum-minimalist style. The room uses an exposed brick cladding wall as the main rustic element with a minimalist interior set-up. The room has the bare essential furniture pieces. The room also uses a natural bamboo wall design that adds an aesthetically pleasing but unusual minimalist interior.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174357\/bedroom-in-rustic-and-minimalist-style.jpg\" alt=\"Bedroom in rustic and minimalist home design with exposed brick cladding wall adds an aesthetically pleasing.\" class=\"wp-image-21981\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174357\/bedroom-in-rustic-and-minimalist-style.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174357\/bedroom-in-rustic-and-minimalist-style-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174357\/bedroom-in-rustic-and-minimalist-style-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174357\/bedroom-in-rustic-and-minimalist-style-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The bedroom depicts the perfect blend of rustic and minimalist interior design<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Add Warmth To Your Minimalist Home Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Minimalism comes with crisp and clean design lines with basic and only essential elements in the interiors. And though the minimalist design looks great, it can be a bit soulless at times. Enliven your minimalist home designs with vibrant and warm elements. You can go with a mix of shades and textures to incorporate some homely vibe in your place. For this, you can choose a warm colour tone and apply it to the monochromatic minimalist colour scheme of your room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174403\/bedroom-interior-design-in-minimalist-style-with-blue-wardrobe.jpg\" alt=\"White bedroom in a minimalist home designed with turquoise blue wardrobe colour creates crisp and clean design.\" class=\"wp-image-21982\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174403\/bedroom-interior-design-in-minimalist-style-with-blue-wardrobe.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174403\/bedroom-interior-design-in-minimalist-style-with-blue-wardrobe-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174403\/bedroom-interior-design-in-minimalist-style-with-blue-wardrobe-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174403\/bedroom-interior-design-in-minimalist-style-with-blue-wardrobe-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A minimalist, white bedroom design with a refreshing twist of turquoise blue colour<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tweak Minimalism With Natural Green Plants<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Green indoor plants will come as a breath of fresh air in your minimalist home design. The right thing to do here is find the balance and decide the green elements as per your room\u2019s form and structure. If you have a small space, you can add a couple of small planters to the room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174433\/minimalist-home-design-with-natural-plant.jpg\" alt=\"White open living room in minimalist home design with natural indoor plants brings a freshness to the area.\" class=\"wp-image-21987\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174433\/minimalist-home-design-with-natural-plant.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174433\/minimalist-home-design-with-natural-plant-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174433\/minimalist-home-design-with-natural-plant-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174433\/minimalist-home-design-with-natural-plant-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A white open living area with biophilic design elements<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Simplify Your Bathroom Too With A Minimalist Home Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The bathroom shown here uses a monochrome white colour scheme with a mix of tile and brick cladding wall designs. Everything else is kept subtle in the bathroom with an elegant patchwork tile flooring that adds character to the bathroom. The bathroom also comes with a modular vanity unit with handleless cabinets that conform to minimal designs. You can try this type of minimalist theme for both small and big bathrooms.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174502\/white-bathroom-design-in-minimalist-style.jpg\" alt=\"Monochrome white bathroom in minimalist home design with a mix of tile and brick cladding wall adds character.\" class=\"wp-image-21992\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174502\/white-bathroom-design-in-minimalist-style.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174502\/white-bathroom-design-in-minimalist-style-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174502\/white-bathroom-design-in-minimalist-style-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/19174502\/white-bathroom-design-in-minimalist-style-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A white bathroom design with clean design lines and uncluttered arrangements<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Minimalist home design is all about understanding your necessities and keeping everything simple. However, it is never about tedious and dull interiors. So, we\u2019d say, take chances and experiment with different elements without overstating any angle. The charm is to underplay monochromatic schemes and clean design lines to create simple and uncluttered spaces.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content